28/08/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The leaders of the four parties in the ruling coalition in Federation BiH (FBiH) -- Sulejman Tihic of the Party of Democratic Action, Haris Silajdzic of the Party for BiH, Dragan Covic of the Croatian Democratic Union (HDZ) and Damir Ljubic, deputy chairman of HDZ 1990 -- met on Monday (August 28th) in Sarajevo with FBiH Prime Minister Nedzad Brankovic to co-ordinate the government's main goals.
They agreed that 19 important reform laws should be adopted by the end of September.
The most important of these deal with income and profit tax, social contributions and privatisation.
The leaders agreed that the FBiH parliament must intensify efforts in September to accomplish these tasks.
They also pledged that the draft 2008 budget law will be ready and tabled in parliamentary procedure by the end of October.
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine -- 28/08/07;
RTRS, Fena - 27/08/07)
